member.returns:
Returns true if the specified feature is
supported on this node, false otherwise.
@since DOM Level 2

true if this node has any attributes,
false otherwise.
@since DOM Level 2

The Attr value as a string, or the empty string
if that attribute does not have a specified or default value.
@since DOM Level 2

member.summary:
If an attempt is made to use an object that is not, or is no longer,
usable.
@since DOM Level 2

If an attempt is made to create or change an object in a way which is
incorrect with regard to namespaces.
@since DOM Level 2

If a parameter or an operation is not supported by the underlying
object.
@since DOM Level 2

member.returns:
A new NodeList object containing all the matched
Elements.
@since DOM Level 2

member.summary:
The Element node this attribute is attached to or
null if this attribute is not in use.
@since DOM Level 2
